value.value: Abnormální vzorec chůze, který vzniká ze slabosti pretibiálních a peroneálních svalů v důsledku léze nižšího motorického neuronu. Postižení pacienti mají pokles nohy a nejsou schopni dorsiflexe a evertovat nohu. Noha je při chůzi zvednuta vysoko aby prsty byly nad zemí a když noha znovu dopadne na zem, může se ozývat pleskání.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: An abnormal gait pattern that arises from weakness of the pretibial and peroneal muscles due to a lower motor neuron lesion. Affected patients have footdrop and are unable to dorsiflex and evert the foot. The leg is lifted high on walking so that the toes clear the ground, and there may be a slapping noise when the foot strikes the ground again.

value.value: Alt motor nöron lezyonu nedeniyle pretibial ve peroneal kasların güçsüzlüğünden kaynaklanan anormal bir yürüyüş örneği. Bu hastalıktan müzdarip hastalar footdrop sendromuna sahiptir ve ayaklarını ileri atıp çeviremezler. Bacak yürürken havada kalır bu yüzdende ayak parmakları yerde sürünür, ve ayak tekrardan yere vurduğu zaman şaplak sesi bile çıkabilir

definition.value: This finding is typically demonstrated by nerve biopsy. Following focal damage to an axon, the part of the axon that is distal to the lesion invariably degenerates, a process that is known as anterograde (or Wallerian) degeneration. During Wallerian degeneration, often a microenvironment is created that can allow successful regrowth of nerve fibers from the proximal nerve segment.

value.value: A compound muscle action potential (CMAP) is a type of electromyography (EMG). CMAP refers to a group of almost simultaneous action potentials from several muscle fibers in the same area evoked by stimulation of the supplying motor nerve and are recorded as one multipeaked summated action potential. This abnormality refers to a greater than normal decrease in the amplitude during the course of the investigation.

Birleşik kas hareket potansiyeli (CMAP), bir çeşit elektromiyografidir (EMG). CMAP, motor sinir uyarımı ile uyandırılan aynı bölgedeki birkaç kas lifinden hemen hemen eş zamanlı hareket potansiyelleri grubunu ifade eder ve birçok eylem potansiyeli olduğu kaydedilir. Bu anormallik, araştırma süresince genlikte anormal bir artışı ifade eder

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: A compound muscle action potential (CMAP) is a type of electromyography (EMG). CMAP refers to a group of almost simultaneous action potentials from several muscle fibers in the same area evoked by stimulation of the supplying motor nerve and are recorded as one multipeaked summated action potential. value.value: Sumační svalový akční potenciá (compound muscle action potential, CMAP) je druh elektromyografie (EMG). CMAP označuje skupinu téměř současných akčních potenciálů z několika svalových vláken ve stejné oblasti vyvolaných stimulací zásobujícího motorického nervu a jsou zaznamenávány jako jeden vícevrcholový sumovaný akční potenciál. Tato abnormalita se týká většího než normálního poklesu amplitudy v průběhu vyšetřování.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: A compound muscle action potential (CMAP) is a type of electromyography (EMG). CMAP refers to a group of almost simultaneous action potentials from several muscle fibers in the same area evoked by stimulation of the supplying motor nerve and are recorded as one multipeaked summated action potential. This abnormality refers to a greater than normal decrease in the amplitude during the course of the investigation.

definition.value: The result of this test is abnormal if progressively fewer muscle fibers respond to nerve stimulation during a train of stimuli, thereby yielding a decrementing pattern in the CMAP.
